The manipulator can be equipped with various end-effectors such as grippers, vacuum cups, clamps, or custom fixtures depending on the part geometry and application requirements. In this production line, grippers will be used as end-effector.</t></si><si><t>908_M10_MCD_PRC150_00</t></si><si><t>Cold inspected part</t></si><si><t>908_M10_MCD_PRC150_00 &amp; 908_M10_MCD_PRC160_00</t></si><si><t>Cold inspected part &amp; Hot Nosing Preform</t></si><si><t>The Hot Nosing Preform CNC operation is performed to prepare parts for the subsequent nose forming process by accurately machining the required outer diameter and reference surfaces.
During this operation, the part is clamped from the internal diameter using a chuck and supported from the opposite side with a tailstock center. In the first stage, the outer diameter is machined to the specified dimensions while ensuring concentricity with the internal reference.
